FBIS4-40551 "drsov117_a_94010" FBIS-SOV-94-117 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS State Duma Speaker Favors International Forum on DPRK State Duma Speaker Favors International Forum on DPRK LD1606160794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1353 GMT 16 Jun 94 LD1606160794 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] Duma Speaker Ivan Rybkin spoke out in favor of Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev's call for a conference on the Korean peninsula. Talking to journalists in Bonn on Thursday, he said that even if sanctions were imposed on North Korea, they should be implemented in stages. In his opinion, sanctions could be applied only after stern warnings. Meanwhile, the head of the Duma's International Affairs Committee Vladimir Lukin said that the lower house expects Kozyrev to report on the situation in North Korea on Friday. And on June 20, the committee will hear from the ambassadors of the countries concerned.
